{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T08:45:25.116Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "DataLoader & Datasets — concept overview"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What DataLoader & Datasets Are"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "In PyTorch, "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}, {"type": "code"}], "text": "Dataset"}, {"type": "text", "text": " and "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}, {"type": "code"}], "text": "DataLoader"}, {"type": "text", "text": " are two essential data handling abstractions from "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "torch.utils.data"}, {"type": "text", "text": " that make data loading, batching, and preprocessing easy for training deep learning models."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Think of them as:\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}, {"type": "code"}], "text": "Dataset"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": A big basket holding all your data (images, labels, text) that gives you one piece at a time when asked\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}, {"type": "code"}], "text": "DataLoader"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": A server that takes the basket and serves data to your model in batches (e.g., 32 images at once) with shuffling and parallel loading"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Together, they make training smooth and fast by abstracting data management."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why They Matter in Generative AI"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Efficient data loading is "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "crucial"}, {"type": "text", "text": " for training generative models because:"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Challenge"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Solution"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Training on massive datasets (millions of images for GANs, diffusion)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "DataLoader"}, {"type": "text", "text": " batches data efficiently"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "GPU memory limits require controlled batch sizes"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "batch_size"}, {"type": "text", "text": " parameter controls memory usage"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Models need diverse data patterns (not ordered sequences)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "shuffle=True"}, {"type": "text", "text": " randomizes data order"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Data loading slower than GPU computation"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "num_workers"}, {"type": "text", "text": " enables multiprocessing"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Custom data formats (medical images, art datasets)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Create custom "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "Dataset"}, {"type": "text", "text": " classes"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Real-time augmentation (flips, crops, colors)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Apply "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "transforms"}, {"type": "text", "text": " on-the-fly"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "They enable efficient data management, batching, shuffling, and parallel loading—essential for training large-scale generative models."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How Dataset Works"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "Dataset"}, {"type": "text", "text": " Class"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "Dataset"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is an "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "abstract class"}, {"type": "text", "text": " representing your dataset. You use built-in datasets (MNIST, CIFAR) or create your own by extending it."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Three required methods"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (map-style datasets):"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "from torch.utils.data import Dataset\n\nclass MyDataset(Dataset):\n    def __init__(self):\n        # Load data (from files, folders, CSV, etc.)\n        self.data = load_my_data()  # [web:31]\n        self.labels = load_my_labels()\n    \n    def __len__(self):\n        # Return total number of samples\n        return len(self.data)  # [web:31][web:32]\n    \n    def __getitem__(self, index):\n        # Return one sample + label at index\n        sample = self.data[index]\n        label = self.labels[index]\n        return sample, label  # [web:31][web:32]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "You must override:\n1. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}, {"type": "code"}], "text": "__init__"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Initialize and load data\n2. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}, {"type": "code"}], "text": "__len__"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Return dataset size\n3. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}, {"type": "code"}], "text": "__getitem__"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Retrieve sample at index"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Two Types of Datasets"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Type"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Methods"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use Case"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Map-style"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "__getitem__()"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "__len__()"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Images, custom data"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Iterable-style"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "__iter__()"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Streaming, large text datasets"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Most generative AI uses "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "map-style"}, {"type": "text", "text": " datasets."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Creating Custom Dataset with Transforms"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "from torchvision import transforms\n\nclass ImageDataset(Dataset):\n    def __init__(self, root_dir, transforms=None):\n        self.images = list_images(root_dir)\n        self.transforms = transforms\n    \n    def __len__(self):\n        return len(self.images)\n    \n    def __getitem__(self, idx):\n        # Load image\n        image = load_image(self.images[idx])\n        \n        # Apply preprocessing (on-the-fly)\n        if self.transforms:\n            image = self.transforms(image)\n        \n        return image\n\n# Define transforms for generative training\ntransforms = transforms.Compose([\n    transforms.Resize((256, 256)),\n    transforms.RandomHorizontalFlip(),\n    transforms.ColorJitter(brightness=0.2, contrast=0.2),\n    transforms.ToTensor()  # Convert to PyTorch tensor [web:32]\n])\n\ndataset = ImageDataset(\"/path/to/images\", transforms=transforms)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How DataLoader Works"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "DataLoader"}, {"type": "text", "text": " Class"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "DataLoader"}, {"type": "text", "text": " wraps your dataset and enables "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "batching, shuffling, and multi-threaded loading"}, {"type": "text", "text": "."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "from torch.utils.data import DataLoader\n\ntrain_loader = DataLoader(\n    dataset=dataset,       # Your Dataset object [web:30]\n    batch_size=32,         # Samples per batch [web:32][web:35]\n    shuffle=True,          # Shuffle data [web:30][web:35]\n    num_workers=2,         # Subprocesses for loading [web:30][web:35]\n    pin_memory=True,       # Faster GPU transfer [web:30]\n    drop_last=True         # Drop incomplete batch [web:30]\n)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key Parameters"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Parameter"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Purpose"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Typical Value"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "dataset"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Dataset to load from"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Your "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "Dataset"}, {"type": "text", "text": " instance"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "batch_size"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Samples per batch"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "32, 64, 128"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "shuffle"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Randomize order"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "True"}, {"type": "text", "text": " for training"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "num_workers"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Parallel loading processes"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "2-8 (CPU cores)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "pin_memory"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Faster GPU transfer"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "True"}, {"type": "text", "text": " for GPU training"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "drop_last"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Drop incomplete batch"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "True"}, {"type": "text", "text": " for consistent batches"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "collate_fn"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Custom batching logic"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For text/custom data"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Iterating Over DataLoader"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# DataLoader calls __getitem__() and wraps for batch [web:33]\nfor batch_idx, (images, labels) in enumerate(train_loader):\n    # images: tensor of shape (batch_size, channels, H, W)\n    # labels: tensor of shape (batch_size,)\n    \n    # Forward pass\n    outputs = model(images)\n    loss = loss_fn(outputs, labels)\n    \n    # Backward pass\n    loss.backward()\n    optimizer.step()"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The DataLoader just calls "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "__getitem__()"}, {"type": "text", "text": " from the Dataset and wraps for the entire batch during training."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Integration with Tensors, Autograd, and Modules"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Complete Training Pipeline"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import torch\nimport torch.nn as nn\nfrom torch.utils.data import Dataset, DataLoader\n\n# 1. Define Dataset\nclass GANDataset(Dataset):\n    def __init__(self, image_path):\n        self.images = load_images(image_path)\n    \n    def __len__(self):\n        return len(self.images)\n    \n    def __getitem__(self, idx):\n        image = self.images[idx]\n        image = preprocess(image)  # Convert to tensor\n        return image\n\n# 2. Define Model (nn.Module)\nclass Generator(nn.Module):\n    def __init__(self):\n        super().__init__()\n        self.network = nn.Sequential(\n            nn.Linear(128, 256),\n            nn.ReLU(),\n            nn.Linear(256, 784)\n        )\n    \n    def forward(self, x):\n        return self.network(x)\n\n# 3. Create DataLoader\ndataset = GANDataset(\"/path/to/training-images\")\ntrain_loader = DataLoader(\n    dataset,\n    batch_size=64,\n    shuffle=True,\n    num_workers=4\n)\n\n# 4. Training loop (Tensors + Autograd)\nmodel = Generator()\noptimizer = torch.optim.Adam(model.parameters(), lr=0.001)\n\nfor epoch in range(100):\n    for batch_idx, real_images in enumerate(train_loader):\n        # real_images is a tensor (64, 3, 256, 256)\n        \n        # Generate fake images\n        noise = torch.randn(64, 128)\n        fake_images = model(noise)\n        \n        # Compute loss (Tensor operation)\n        loss = compute_gan_loss(fake_images, real_images)\n        \n        # Backpropagate (Autograd computes gradients)\n        loss.backward()  # [web:1]\n        optimizer.step()"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Built-in Datasets"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "PyTorch provides ready-made datasets in "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "torchvision"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "torchaudio"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", and "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "torchtext"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "from torchvision.datasets import MNIST, CIFAR10, FashionMNIST\nfrom torch.utils.data import DataLoader\n\n# MNIST (for simple GAN demos)\nmnist = MNIST(root=\"./data\", download=True, train=True)\ntrain_loader = DataLoader(mnist, batch_size=32, shuffle=True)\n\n# CIFAR-10 (for more complex generative models)\ncifar = CIFAR10(root=\"./data\", download=True, train=True)\ntrain_loader = DataLoader(cifar, batch_size=64, shuffle=True, num_workers=4)\n\n# ImageFolder (generic for custom image datasets)\nfrom torchvision.datasets import ImageFolder\ndataset = ImageFolder(root=\"/path/to/images\")\nloader = DataLoader(dataset, batch_size=32, shuffle=True)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "All datasets under "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "torchvision.datasets"}, {"type": "text", "text": " are subclasses of "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "torch.utils.data.Dataset"}, {"type": "text", "text": " with "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "__len__()"}, {"type": "text", "text": " and "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "__getitem__()"}, {"type": "text", "text": " implemented."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mental Model"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Think of Dataset + DataLoader as a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "restaurant kitchen system"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"start": 1, "type": null}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Dataset = Ingredient storage"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Contains all raw ingredients (images), organized with labels"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}, {"type": "code"}], "text": "__getitem__(idx)"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Chef fetches one ingredient at a specific location"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}, {"type": "code"}], "text": "__len__()"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Inventory count of total ingredients"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "DataLoader = Assembly line"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Takes ingredients from storage and serves them in batches to the cook"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}, {"type": "code"}], "text": "batch_size=32"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Cook gets 32 plates at once (not one by one)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}, {"type": "code"}], "text": "shuffle=True"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Randomize order so cook doesn't memorize sequences"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}, {"type": "code"}], "text": "num_workers=4"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": 4 chefs fetch ingredients simultaneously (parallel loading)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Model = The cook"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Processes batches to create the dish (training)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "This abstraction lets you focus on model design, not data handling."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key Takeaways"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}, {"type": "code"}], "text": "Dataset"}, {"type": "text", "text": " abstracts your data (X and y) into an object with "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "__getitem__()"}, {"type": "text", "text": " and "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "__len__()"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}, {"type": "code"}], "text": "DataLoader"}, {"type": "text", "text": " wraps Dataset to serve data in mini-batches with shuffling and parallel loading"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Map-style datasets"}, {"type": "text", "text": " require "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "__getitem__(idx)"}, {"type": "text", "text": " and "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "__len__()"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Custom datasets"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Extend "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "Dataset"}, {"type": "text", "text": " and override the three methods"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}, {"type": "code"}], "text": "batch_size"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Controls how many samples per batch (critical for GPU memory)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}, {"type": "code"}], "text": "shuffle=True"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Randomizes data order for better training"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}, {"type": "code"}], "text": "num_workers"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Enables multiprocessing for faster data loading"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Built-in datasets"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Use "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "torchvision.datasets"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (MNIST, CIFAR, ImageFolder)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Transforms"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Apply preprocessing (resize, flip, color jitter) on-the-fly"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Essential for generative AI"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Efficient loading of large image/text datasets for GANs, diffusion, LLMs"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Dataset tells PyTorch "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "how"}, {"type": "text", "text": " to get your data, DataLoader helps you "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "serve it in batches"}, {"type": "text", "text": "—Together they make training smooth and fast for any deep learning project."}]}]}}